Proprietà CTI (Clicca per espandere) Proprietà Dettagli tags • Backdoor language Javascript C2 Y http encryption • AES• ECDH capabilities • Exfiltration• Screen Capture• Audio Recording Commands dst_countries origin data collected MainBranch • DarkSword threat_actor • UNC6748 date_detection 2025-12-01 target_industry • Users <p>GHOSTKNIFE writes files to disk during its execution under <code>/tmp/&lt;uuid&gt;.&lt;numbers&gt;</code>, where <code>uuid</code> is a randomly generated UUIDv4 value and <code>numbers</code> is a hard-coded sequence of several digits. Under that directory, it creates multiple subfolders including <code>STORAGE</code>, <code>DATA</code>, and <code>TMP</code>. As each module of GHOSTKNIFE executes, it writes its data to <code>/tmp/&lt;uuid&gt;.&lt;numbers&gt;/STORAGE/&lt;uuid2&gt;.&lt;id&gt;</code>, where <code>id</code> is the numeric value of the module and <code>uuid2</code> is a different randomly generated UUIDv4 value. Additionally, GHOSTKNIFE periodically erases crash logs from the device to cover its tracks in case of unexpected failures. <pre><code> cleanLogs(){ 
       let files =  MyHelper.getContentsOfDir("/var/mobile/Library/Logs/CrashReporter/"); 
       for(let file of files){//.ips  // mediaplaybackd-" panic-full- 
        if(file.includes("mediaplaybackd") || file.includes("SpringBoard") || file.includes("com.apple.WebKit.") || file.includes("panic-full-") ){ 
          MyHelper.deleteFileAtPath(file); 
        } 
       } 
  }
</code></pre></p>
